.container.process-steps
  h2.text-center Our process
  .row
    .col-md-10.col-sm-offset-1
      .row
        .col-sm-4.text-center
          br
          br
          .center-block
            em.icon-directions(style="font-size:140px;color:#C1CEDE;")
        .col-sm-8
          h3 Routing
          p To ensure smooth service on a snow day, and a smooth season overall, we are meticulous with planning and organizing our winter routes. All of our drivers complete at least two practice runs before a single snowflake even hits the ground so that they are well acquainted with the route.
          p To ensure that our drivers can easily spot your property on service day, we install stakes in the lawn next to your driveway. The marker also indicates the edge of your driveway and helps protect your lawn from getting scraped by the plows or blowers.
      hr
      .row
        .col-sm-4.col-sm-push-8.text-center
          br
          br
          div.center-block(skycon="snow", color="#C1CEDE", width="140", height="140")
        .col-sm-8.col-sm-pull-4.text-right
          h3 Weather Watch
          p During the winter season, we actively monitor the weather for any possible snow events. We post frequent updates whenever there is a potential of snow, so that our clients can always be certain whether we will be servicing.
          p Since our crews are dispatched only after two inches of snow has accumulated, we always take into consideration the different areas of our territory. Sometimes the lake effects causes flurries near the water, while other times, it sends the clouds further north.
      hr
      .row
        .col-sm-4.text-center
          br
          br
          .center-block(style='-ms-transform: rotate(-7deg);-webkit-transform: rotate(-7deg);transform: rotate(-7deg);')
            em.icon-earphones-alt(style="font-size:140px;color:#C1CEDE;")
        .col-sm-8
          h3 Dispatch
          p Once two inches of snow has fallen, our crews are sent to their routes. Each route is covered by a dedicated plow driver and a shoveller. We continuously update and optimize our routes to ensure efficient service and the fastest possible service times.
          p Our office staff monitor our crews’ progress with GPS tracking installed in all vehicles. In case of any slowdowns or breakdowns, our staff are able to assign nearby vehicles to service any outstanding properties.
      hr
      .row
        .col-sm-4.col-sm-push-8.text-center
          br
          br
          .center-block(style='-ms-transform: rotate(7deg);-webkit-transform: rotate(7deg);transform: rotate(7deg);')
            em.icon-bell(style="font-size:140px;color:#C1CEDE;")
        .col-sm-8.col-sm-pull-4.text-right
          h3 Communication & Followup
          p As soon as a property has been serviced, the client is sent an automated email - provided that an email exists on file.
          p We post all service updates online as soon as they become available, including potential storms, partial service days, and full service updates. In cases of severe weather and extraneous circumstances, we post more detailed and more frequent updates regarding any relevant information.
          p In any event, our call center is available around the clock to address any questions or concerns directly over the phone.
